10. Testing and Evaluation. Manual Testing (Stage 5)
10.1 Test Cases

Board initialisation

Step: Open game in browser.
Expected result: 8×8 board displayed, 4 starting pieces in centre.
Actual result: Board displayed correctly with 4 pieces.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Normalise board

Steps: Check all board cells.
Expected result: All cells have constants: DARK, LIGHT, or NONE.
Actual result: All cells normalised correctly.
Pass or Fail:  Pass.
Legal move
Steps: Place your dark piece on a legal square that flips the opponent piece(s).
Expected result: Opponent piece(s) flipped to DARK.
Actual result: Piece(s) flipped correctly.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Illegal move

Steps: Place your dark piece at a square with no flips, which is illegal. 
Expected result: Error message shown; move rejected.
Actual result: Error message shown (move is illegal), move rejected.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

AI opponent move

Steps: After the player places a dark piece.
Expected result: AI opponent, which plays with light pieces, chooses a legal move randomly.
Actual result: AI opponent moved to valid square.
Pass or Fail:  Pass.

Move counter

Steps: Make a move.
Expected result: Move counter decreases by 1.
Actual result: Move counter decreased correctly.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Game over (when board is full)

Steps: Fill the board completely with pieces.
Expected result: The game determines the winner correctly or declares a tie; a message is           shown.
Actual result: Winner or tie message is displayed correctly.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Game over (when both players have no legal moves)

Steps: Leave no legal moves for either player.
Expected result: Game ends, tie or winner declared.
Actual result: Game over message shown.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Save game

Steps: Click save button.
Expected result: Game states that it is successfully saved.
Actual result: File created and data correct.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Load game

Steps: Click the load button.
Expected result: Previously saved game restored.
Actual result: Board and move counter restored correctly.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Invalid load

Steps: Delete JSON file and click on load button.
Expected result: Error message displayed, but game creates a new save file or continues without crashing.
Actual result: Correct error message shown, new JSON file created and game continues as normal.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

Count pieces

Steps: Call count_pieces(board).
Expected result: Returns correct number of DARK and LIGHT.
Actual result: Count correctly pieces.
Pass or Fail:  Pass.

Outflank flip logic

Steps: Make a move that flips multiple directions.
Expected result: All outflanked pieces flipped.
Actual result: Pieces flipped correctly.
Pass or Fail: Pass.

10.2 Detailed Information

The test cases written in 10.1 test if the Othello game works correctly, if it follows the rules, checks AI logic, game progression, error handling and if saving/load works properly. In the “Actual result” I wrote about what actually happens when you try the test in the browser and in the “Pass or fail” I wrote Pass if it works, otherwise Fail.





